    "To discriminate among the various proposed scenarios, or unveil new ones, several groups have put considerable effort into studying BBH populations (Abbott et al. 2019 (Abbott et al., 2021b (Abbott et al., 2023c;; Talbot & Thrane 2018; Stevenson et al. 2019; Edelman et al. 2021; Fishbach et al. 2021; Roulet et al. 2021; Galaudage et al. 2021; Bouffanais et al. 2021; Stevenson & Clarke 2022; Callister & Farr 2024; Sadiq et al. 2024).",
    "Current theoretical models propose several different formation channels for astrophysical BBHs.",
    "Among those, the most highly considered in the literature are isolated evolution (e.g.",
    "Bethe & Brown 1998; Belczynski et al. 2002; Dominik et al. 2012; Eldridge & Stanway 2016; Stevenson et al. 2017; Klencki et al. 2018; Kruckow et al. 2018; Iorio et al. 2023; Fragos et al. 2023; Briel et al. 2023; Srinivasan et al. 2023) and dynamical assembly in star clusters (e.g.",
